hu, they were decorated by Her Majesty the Queen. In this contemplative memoir, Tony describes Bhutan in rich detail at a transformative period in its history and reflects on tradition, belief, modernization, and happiness. See the book trailer at: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g-VsWAbTHAQ  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCollege teacherszBhutanvBiography. 0aCollege teacherszCanadavBiography. 0aEducationzBhutan. 0aFund raisingzBhutan. 0aRunning raceszBhutan. 7aTravel / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  aTravel Writing / Literature / Bhutan.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212351740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772123517423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772123517/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles